descript.abstract: Speed limit column was added to a 1998 street centerline shapefile. Speed limits are indicated primarily for streets that have speeds higher than 25 MPH. 25 MPH is the de facto speed limit for residential and most commercial streets. Alleys narrower than 25 feet can have de facto speed limits of 15 MPH. The latter are not indicated specifically in this shapefile.
descript.purpose: Record speed limits for enforcement and monitoring purposes. Updated as speed limits are modified over time.
descript.supplinf: Zero speed limit = De Facto California Vehicle Code speed limit (typically 25 MPH)
